data.oai_dc:dc: FIG. 5. Phylogenies for all Tremadocian through Darriwilian crinoids with all taxa used in Ausich et al. (in press, Fig. 2B), plus Adelphicrinus, Cnemecrinus, and Eknomocrinus. All results from PAUP 4.0a142, all analyses resulted from heuristic search with random addition and 1000 repetitions. A, strict consensus of 514 most-parsimonious trees, tree length 447, CI=0.465, RI=0.564, RC=0.262, B, 50% majority-rule tree of Fig. 5A.
